## Case study: From hourly to leveraged

Sarah was a marketing freelancer at $100/hour, capped at $12K/month. Burned out. Income was wildly variable.

**Her fix:** Productized her most common project: "Launch Accelerator" — $5K, 6-week engagement for course creators.

**Timeline:**
- Month 1-2: Refined process, built templates. One $5K project each month.
- Month 3-6: Settled into 1-2 launches/month = $8-10K/month, working 25 hrs/week instead of 40.
- Added a $300 "Launch Checklist" PDF as front-end product = $500-800/month additional.

**By month 12:** $13K/month revenue (freelance peak), but 30-35 hrs/week instead of 40-50, with low burnout.

**Key insight:** She didn't build SaaS. She just stopped trading 1 hour = $100. Productizing removed the ceiling.

---

## Key mistakes to avoid

**Chasing trends.** Everyone talks SaaS or courses? Doesn't matter if your skills are in services. Bad match = failure.

**Starting too complex.** Pick one model. Master it. Don't spin up freelancing + productized + course + membership simultaneously.

**Ignoring lifestyle fit.** A model making $100K/month but requiring 24/7 availability is a job, not a business.

---

## FAQ

**Can I start with one model and switch later?**
Yes. Start fast-to-revenue (freelancing or productized), then layer digital products. Don't start with SaaS.

**Which model gets to $5K/month fastest?**
Productized service or consulting retainer. Both 2-4 months with existing skills.

**Which gives the most time freedom?**
Hybrid: productized service (40% revenue, 20 hrs/week) + affiliate/course (60% revenue, 5 hrs/week).

**Can I really make $50K+ solo?**
Yes. Consulting retainers, premium productized services, hybrid models all work. SaaS possible but requires deep technical commitment.

